ONLINE IN AN HOUR.

170
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:29,848
WELL, MAYBE IF YOU HAD
MORE HELP?

171
00:06:29,932 --> 00:06:32,142
WHY DO YOU WANNA BE
ON THE NEWSPAPER SO BADLY?

172
00:06:32,226 --> 00:06:33,810
(SIGHS)

173
00:06:33,894 --> 00:06:38,148
CLARE:
LAST SEMESTER WAS A COMPLETE
TRAIN WRECK FOR ME.

174
00:06:38,232 --> 00:06:39,233
MY BOYFRIEND...

175
00:06:42,069 --> 00:06:47,115
MY EX-BOYFRIEND ELI AND I
HAD A TERRIBLE BREAK-UP.

176
00:06:47,199 --> 00:06:48,700
ARE YOU SERIOUSLY CRYING
RIGHT NOW?

177
00:06:48,784 --> 00:06:50,827
ALL I WANT IS TO MOVE ON!

178
00:06:50,911 --> 00:06:52,204
OKAY, YOU CAN'T KEEP ME
OFF THIS PAPER

179
00:06:52,287 --> 00:06:54,039
BECAUSE I MADE ONE MISTAKE.

180
00:06:54,122 --> 00:06:55,499
I AM A GOOD WRITER!

181
00:06:55,582 --> 00:06:58,168
IF YOU LET ME ON,
I WILL DO WHATEVER YOU SAY.

182
00:06:58,252 --> 00:06:59,336
YOU'LL DO WHATEVER
I SAY?

183
00:06:59,419 --> 00:07:01,296
YES! I PROMISE.

184
00:07:01,380 --> 00:07:04,216
OKAY, THEN WIPE AWAY
THOSE DRAMA QUEEN TEARS

185
00:07:04,299 --> 00:07:05,843
AND LEAVE ME ALONE

186
00:07:05,926 --> 00:07:08,262
SO I CAN POST THIS PAPER!

187
00:07:08,345 --> 00:07:09,721
(SIGHS DEEPLY)

188
00:07:09,805 --> 00:07:11,807
DOES THAT MEAN YOU'LL GIVE ME
A SECOND CHANCE?

189
00:07:11,890 --> 00:07:12,933
NO!

190
00:07:13,016 --> 00:07:15,644
IT MEANS I NEED YOU
OUT OF MY FACE!

191
00:07:15,727 --> 00:07:17,604
YOU HAD YOUR CHANCE,
CLARE.

192
00:07:18,605 --> 00:07:19,606
BYE.

193
00:07:23,902 --> 00:07:26,572
♪ You've got such a good ear ♪

194
00:07:27,573 --> 00:07:28,949
♪ Why won't you listen ♪

195
00:07:29,950 --> 00:07:31,368
(TAXI DOOR SLAMS)

196
00:07:34,663 --> 00:07:36,373
HEY, CHARLIE.

197
00:07:36,456 --> 00:07:39,501
HEY, FIONA,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

198
00:07:39,585 --> 00:07:41,795
I SAW THE FIGHT.
ARE YOU OKAY?

199
00:07:42,796 --> 00:07:45,299
YEAH,
JUST SOME PERSONAL STUFF.

200
00:07:46,300 --> 00:07:47,467
FIONA:
DO YOU WANNA TALK
ABOUT IT?

201
00:07:47,551 --> 00:07:48,552
NO, I DON'T.

202
00:07:50,262 --> 00:07:52,264
WE COULD GET LUNCH,
MY TREAT.

203
00:07:52,347 --> 00:07:54,224
CHARLIE:
I CAN'T.

204
00:07:54,308 --> 00:07:57,728
I HAVE SOME THINGS
I HAVE TO TAKE CARE OF.

205
00:07:57,811 --> 00:07:59,062
YOU LOOK LIKE
YOU NEED A FRIEND.

206
00:07:59,146 --> 00:08:00,522
THERE'S GOTTA BE SOMETHING
I CAN DO.

207
00:08:00,606 --> 00:08:03,942
JUST GO BACK TO HIGH SCHOOL,
OKAY, FIONA?

208
00:08:07,112 --> 00:08:08,113
(SIGHS)

209
00:08:10,365 --> 00:08:12,910
PEOPLE SURE ARE RILED UP
WITH THIS WHOLE DAVE THING.

210
00:08:12,993 --> 00:08:15,412
HOW'S YOUR DAY GOING SO FAR?
ANY BACKLASH?

211
00:08:15,495 --> 00:08:16,997
MOSTLY AGAINST DAVE.

212
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:17,998
IT'S WEIRD,

213
00:08:18,081 --> 00:08:18,999
IT'S LIKE I'M IN
THE MIDDLE OF A DEBATE,

214
00:08:19,082 --> 00:08:20,209
AND I HAVEN'T SAID
A THING.

215
00:08:20,292 --> 00:08:21,210
YOU'LL GET YOUR CHANCE
TO TALK,

216
00:08:21,293 --> 00:08:23,003
ONCE YOU'RE ON THE AIR SOLO.

217
00:08:23,086 --> 00:08:24,630
(GIRLS SCREAM)
GIRL: DAVE, GET OUT!

218
00:08:24,713 --> 00:08:25,631
