(SURPRISED MURMURS)
HEY, GUYS! WHOA!

237
00:09:05,629 --> 00:09:06,630
(DAVE GRUNTS)

238
00:09:07,756 --> 00:09:09,216
ELI:
GUYS! SIMPSON!

239
00:09:09,299 --> 00:09:10,467
ALL RIGHT! ALL RIGHT!

240
00:09:10,551 --> 00:09:12,302
ALL RIGHT! ALL RIGHT!

241
00:09:12,386 --> 00:09:16,306
ALL RIGHT, YOU TWO,
WE'RE GOING TO MY OFFICE.

242
00:09:16,390 --> 00:09:17,432
DAVE, I THINK YOUR DAD'S
HERE TODAY,

243
00:09:17,516 --> 00:09:18,642
I THINK I'LL HAVE HIM
JOIN US.

244
00:09:18,725 --> 00:09:19,726
(SIGHS)

245
00:09:21,770 --> 00:09:24,106
MR. SIMPSON:
MY DECISION ON
THE BATHROOM STANDS.

246
00:09:24,189 --> 00:09:25,148
AND FOR YOUR PART
IN THE FIGHT,

247
00:09:25,232 --> 00:09:27,359
WE'LL SEE YOU AFTER SCHOOL.

248
00:09:27,442 --> 00:09:29,611
ADAM:
OKAY. THANK YOU, SIR.

249
00:09:36,451 --> 00:09:37,452
(DOOR SLAMS)

250
00:09:41,456 --> 00:09:43,000
I WANNA SAY MY KID
WOULDN'T DO THIS,

251
00:09:43,083 --> 00:09:44,418
BUT UH...

252
00:09:44,501 --> 00:09:46,503
HERE YOU ARE IN A SKIRT.

253
00:09:46,587 --> 00:09:48,046
SO MUCH FOR BEING
THE MAN.

254
00:09:50,674 --> 00:09:52,843
MR. TURNER,
CARE TO EXPLAIN?

255
00:09:52,926 --> 00:09:54,511
LOOK, I JUST TRIED
TO MAKE A POINT.

256
00:09:54,595 --> 00:09:56,847
BY VIOLATING DRESS CODE
AND FIGHTING IN THE HALLWAY.

257
00:09:56,930 --> 00:09:58,974
SIR, I GOT KICKED OFF THE AIR
FOR HAVING AN OPINION!

258
00:09:59,057 --> 00:10:01,602
YOU GOT KICKED OFF THE AIR
FOR USING OFFENSIVE LANGUAGE.

259
00:10:01,685 --> 00:10:03,145
LOOK, I JUST SAID
WHAT I THOUGHT!

260
00:10:03,228 --> 00:10:04,146
FREE SPEECH!

261
00:10:04,229 --> 00:10:05,189
THAT'S WHAT WE LEARN HERE,
RIGHT?

262
00:10:05,272 --> 00:10:06,190
MR. SIMPSON:
YOU HAVE THE RIGHT
TO FREE SPEECH,

263
00:10:06,273 --> 00:10:08,192
BUT THIS SCHOOL BELONGS
TO ALL OF US,

264
00:10:08,275 --> 00:10:10,027
AND IT HAS TO BE A SAFE
AND COMFORTABLE PLACE

265
00:10:10,110 --> 00:10:11,320
FOR ALL OF US!

266
00:10:11,403 --> 00:10:14,031
YEAH, OR JUST THOSE OF US
THAT MATTER.

267
00:10:14,114 --> 00:10:15,199
(SIGHS HEAVILY)
ALL RIGHT,

268
00:10:15,282 --> 00:10:16,200
YOU WERE IN
THE GIRLS' WASHROOM,

269
00:10:16,283 --> 00:10:17,201
YOU WERE FIGHTING
IN THE HALLWAY,

270
00:10:17,284 --> 00:10:19,578
AND WE'VE ALREADY DISCUSSED
THE RADIO INCIDENT.

271
00:10:19,661 --> 00:10:22,372
YOU CAN THINK ABOUT THIS
IN DETENTION, ALL RIGHT?

272
00:10:22,456 --> 00:10:24,708
SOUNDS ABOUT RIGHT.

273
00:10:24,791 --> 00:10:26,168
AND WHAT,
ADAM GETS OFF SCOTT-FREE?

274
00:10:26,251 --> 00:10:27,628
ADAM WILL BE PUNISHED
FOR FIGHTING TOO.

275
00:10:27,711 --> 00:10:28,629
OKAY,
SO IF WE'RE BOTH WRONG,

276
00:10:28,712 --> 00:10:31,715
THEN WHY CAN'T I GET
MY RADIO JOB BACK?

277
00:10:33,175 --> 00:10:34,218
(SIGHS)

278
00:10:34,301 --> 00:10:36,303
I DON'T THINK
IT'S A GOOD IDEA.

279
00:10:36,386 --> 00:10:37,387
RIGHT.

280
00:10:38,764 --> 00:10:39,890
I LOSE AGAIN.

281
00:10:39,973 --> 00:10:40,933
(BELL RINGS)

282
00:10:41,016 --> 00:10:43,268
KATIE: (OVER PA)
THE DEGRASSI DAILY
IS LOOKING FOR PHOTOGRAPHERS.

283
00:10:43,352 --> 00:10:46,563
PLEASE SUBMIT YOUR PORTFOLIO
TO KATIE MATLIN.

284
00:10:46,647 --> 00:10:47,731
HEY, THERE YOU ARE!

285
00:10:47,814 --> 00:10:49,650
HOW'D TALKING IT OVER
IN PERSON GO?

286
00:10:49,733 --> 00:10:51,068
I WAS REJECTED.

287
00:10:51,151 --> 00:10:53,487
BRUTALLY REJECTED.

288
00:10:53,570 --> 00:10:54,905
I AM SO STUPID.

289
00:10:54,988 --> 00:10:56,448
YOU'RE NOT STUPID.

290
00:10:56,532 --> 00:10:57,449
I THOUGHT THERE
WAS SOMETHING

291
00:10:57,533 --> 00:10:59,076
BETWEEN CHARLIE AND ME,

292
00:10:59,159 --> 00:11:01,912
BUT I WAS JUST A GIRL
HANGING ON.

293
00:11:01,995 --> 00:11:03,539
I COULD DEAL WITH BEING
FRIENDLESS AT DEGRASSI

294
00:11:03,622 --> 00:11:07,417
AS LONG AS I HAD ONE FRIEND
OUTSIDE OF SCHOOL.

295
00:11:07,501 --> 00:11:09,628
WHAT AM I GONNA DO?

296
00:11:09,711 --> 00:11:12,130
YOU FUNCTION BEST
WHEN YOU HAVE A PROJECT.

297
00:11:12,214 --> 00:11:13,257
FORGET ABOUT MAKING FRIENDS

298
00:11:13,340 --> 00:11:15,008
AND JUST FIND
SOMETHING TO DO.

299
00:11:15,092 --> 00:11:17,845
HEY, IT'S BETTER THAN GOING
BACK TO NEW YORK, RIGHT?

300
00:11:17,928 --> 00:11:20,681
RIGHT NOW,
I'M NOT SO SURE.

301
00:11:23,892 --> 00:11:24,977
THANKS A LOT.

302
00:11:25,060 --> 00:11:26,603
WE'RE OFF THE RADIO SHOW
AND IN DETENTION

303
00:11:26,687 --> 00:11:27,688
BECAUSE OF YOU.

304
00:11:29,022 --> 00:11:30,774
THAT'S WHAT YOU
CARE ABOUT?

305
00:11:30,858 --> 00:11:32,818
DO YOU KNOW WHAT SIMPSON
SAID TO ME?

306
00:11:32,901 --> 00:11:34,611
WHAT'D HE DO,
GIVE YOU A LOLLIPOP?

307
00:11:34,695 --> 00:11:36,071
EVER SINCE I GOT HERE,

308
00:11:36,154 --> 00:11:38,407
I'VE BEEN TRYING TO USE
THE GUYS' BATHROOM,

309
00:11:38,490 --> 00:11:40,534
AND NOW I'M BACK
TO THE HANDICAP CRAPPER.

310
00:11:40,617 --> 00:11:41,535
THANKS A LOT.

311
00:11:41,618 --> 00:11:42,786
DAVE:
OOPS! TOUGH LIFE.

312
00:11:42,870 --> 00:11:44,580
SORRY.

313
00:11:44,663 --> 00:11:47,416
HOW COME EVERYONE ELSE
CAN DEAL WITH ME...

314
00:11:47,499 --> 00:11:48,417
EXCEPT YOU?

315
00:11:48,500 --> 00:11:50,752
DAVE:
BECAUSE WHY DO YOU GET
SPECIAL PRIVILEGES?

316
00:11:50,836 --> 00:11:51,753
HOWEVER YOU CUT YOUR HAIR-

317
00:11:51,837 --> 00:11:53,172
ADAM:
IF YOU WANT ME
TO GO INTO THE BORINGNESS

318
00:11:53,255 --> 00:11:54,506
ABOUT TRANSGENDER
BRAIN DEVELOPMENT,

319
00:11:54,590 --> 00:11:55,632
I'D BE GLAD TO.

320
00:11:55,716 --> 00:11:57,217
(SCOFFS) WHATEVER.

321
00:11:59,344 --> 00:12:03,557
EVERY DAY I FIGHT TO DO
THE THINGS YOU DO,

322
00:12:03,640 --> 00:12:05,309
LIKE USE THE GUYS' BATHROOM,

323
00:12:05,392 --> 00:12:06,476
PEE STANDING UP.

324
00:12:06,560 --> 00:12:08,979
YEAH, WHICH YOU SUCK AT,
BY THE WAY.

325
00:12:09,062 --> 00:12:10,314
YOU THINK USING THAT THING
IS EASY?

326
00:12:10,397 --> 00:12:13,066
LOOK, NO ONE MAKES YOU,
ALL RIGHT?

327
00:12:13,150 --> 00:12:14,067
SO YOU HAVE
A DIFFERENT BATHROOM,

328
00:12:14,151 --> 00:12:15,986
BIG DEAL.

329
00:12:16,069 --> 00:12:18,864
HOW WOULD YOU FEEL
IF IT WERE YOU?

330
00:12:18,947 --> 00:12:22,367
I WOULD JUST FOLLOW
THE SIGN ON THE DOOR.

331
00:12:24,745 --> 00:12:25,996
YEAH, WELL, 50 YEARS AGO,

332
00:12:26,079 --> 00:12:28,957
THAT SIGN WOULD'VE SAID
"WHITES ONLY."

333
00:12:29,041 --> 00:12:30,501
THAT'S DIFFERENT!

334
00:12:30,584 --> 00:12:31,668
THAT'S RACISM.

335
00:12:31,752 --> 00:12:34,046
ADAM:
OKAY, MAYBE IT'S NOT
EXACTLY THE SAME,

336
00:12:34,129 --> 00:12:36,048
BUT STILL,
YOU DISCRIMINATED AGAINST ME

337
00:12:36,131 --> 00:12:37,925
BASED ON SOMETHING
I DIDN'T CHOOSE

338
00:12:38,008 --> 00:12:40,177
AND CAN'T CHANGE.

339
00:12:40,260 --> 00:12:42,095
IT'S THE WAY I AM, DAVE.

340
00:12:43,096 --> 00:12:45,933
BUT HEY,
IF YOU'RE OKAY WITH THAT.

341
00:12:49,186 --> 00:12:57,736
♪♪♪

342
00:12:58,737 --> 00:12:59,780
(BUS RUMBLES)

343
00:13:01,323 --> 00:13:03,367
KATIE: (OVER PA)
THE LATEST ISSUE
OF THE DEGRASSI DAILY IS OUT.

344
00:13:03,450 --> 00:13:04,451
PICK YOURS UP TODAY.

345
00:13:04,535 --> 00:13:05,452
ALLI:
SO THAT'S IT?

346
00:13:05,536 --> 00:13:06,870
SHE JUST WON'T LISTEN
TO REASON?

347
00:13:06,954 --> 00:13:08,247
IT'S DEFINITE.

348
00:13:08,330 --> 00:13:10,707
DEGRASSI DAILY'S EDITOR
HATES ME.

349
00:13:10,791 --> 00:13:12,459
WELL, SHE SOUNDS LIKE
A TOTAL "B,"

350
00:13:12,543 --> 00:13:14,545
WITH A SIDE ORDER
OF "ITCH".

351
00:13:14,628 --> 00:13:16,338
OH, COME ON,
KATIE'S ON HONOUR ROLL,

352
00:13:16,421 --> 00:13:18,173
SHE'S A REGIONAL
SOCCER CHAMP.

353
00:13:18,257 --> 00:13:19,174
SHE RAISED THE MOST MONEY

354
00:13:19,258 --> 00:13:20,467
FOR OUR "FREE THE CHILDREN"
CAMPAIGN LAST YEAR,

355
00:13:20,551 --> 00:13:22,427
ALL BY HERSELF.

356
00:13:22,511 --> 00:13:23,428
YOU DON'T GET
WHERE KATIE'S AT

357
00:13:23,512 --> 00:13:25,430
BY LETTING YOUNGER STUDENTS
PUSH YOU AROUND.

358
00:13:25,514 --> 00:13:27,057
WELL,
YOU'RE AN OLDER STUDENT,

359
00:13:27,140 --> 00:13:29,476
NOT TO MENTION THE PRESIDENT
OF THE WHOLE FREAKIN' SCHOOL.

360
00:13:29,560 --> 00:13:31,645
NOW CAN'T YOU GIVE KATIE
A TALKING TO?

361
00:13:33,230 --> 00:13:35,148
MAN, YOU GRADE TENNERS
ARE WEARING ME OUT.

362
00:13:35,232 --> 00:13:36,900
IT'S OKAY, SAV,
I'LL FIND SOME OTHER WAY

363
00:13:36,984 --> 00:13:38,902
TO FILL UP MY SPARE TIME.

364
00:13:38,986 --> 00:13:40,612
BY DOING WHAT?

365
00:13:40,696 --> 00:13:42,364
(CLARE AND ALLI LAUGH)

366
00:13:43,365 --> 00:13:44,533
FIONA!

367
00:13:44,616 --> 00:13:45,534
THANK GOD YOU'RE HERE!

368
00:13:45,617 --> 00:13:48,912
WE ARE FOUR DRAMA NERDS AWAY
FROM VOTING ON A PLAY...

369
00:13:48,996 --> 00:13:50,622
ABOUT A REALITY TV SHOW!

370
00:13:51,623 --> 00:13:53,166
A PLAY...

371
00:13:53,250 --> 00:13:55,085
ABOUT A TV SHOW!

372
00:13:55,169 --> 00:13:56,420
WHAT WOULD I DO?

373
00:13:56,503 --> 00:13:57,546
TALK TO THEM!

374
00:13:57,629 --> 00:14:00,507
YOU'RE THE ONLY PERSON HERE
WITH ANY TASTE!

375
00:14:00,591 --> 00:14:01,884
YEAH,
BUT THEY DON'T KNOW THAT.

376
00:14:01,967 --> 00:14:03,343
THEY DON'T KNOW ME
AT ALL.

377
00:14:03,427 --> 00:14:04,720
PLEASE?

378
00:14:04,803 --> 00:14:05,721
I DON'T WANNA SPEND
ALL SEMESTER

379
00:14:05,804 --> 00:14:07,139
WORKING ON
A PIECE OF CRAP.

380
00:14:07,222 --> 00:14:08,140
MS. DAWES:
OKAY...

381
00:14:08,223 --> 00:14:12,102
LET'S START DISCUSSING
THE CONTENT OF THE PLAY,

382
00:14:12,186 --> 00:14:13,604
THE REALITY...

383
00:14:13,687 --> 00:14:15,022
TV SHOW...THING.

384
00:14:16,064 --> 00:14:17,149
ANY COMMENTS?

385
00:14:19,109 --> 00:14:20,110
PLEASE.

386
00:14:21,403 --> 00:14:23,655
COULD I SAY SOMETHING FIRST?

387
00:14:23,739 --> 00:14:26,116
FIONA, I SUPPOSE SINCE
YOU BOTHERED TO JOIN US

388
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:27,117
IN CLASS TODAY,

389
00:14:27,201 --> 00:14:28,952
YEAH, GO AHEAD.

390
00:14:30,621 --> 00:14:32,456
OKAY,
WHATEVER THE PLAY IS,

391
00:14:32,539 --> 00:14:33,957
IT SHOULD BE REAL.

392
00:14:34,041 --> 00:14:37,211
ABOUT STUFF THAT HAPPENS
TO PEOPLE OUR AGE.

393
00:14:38,212 --> 00:14:41,173
LIKE BEING SCARED
YOU WON'T FIT IN,

394
00:14:42,925 --> 00:14:44,593
FEELING ALONE,

395
00:14:46,178 --> 00:14:48,972
OR BEING COMPLETELY AWKWARD.

396
00:14:49,056 --> 00:14:50,641
LIKE I AM RIGHT NOW.

397
00:14:50,724 --> 00:14:51,767
(A FEW STUDENTS LAUGH)

398
00:14:51,850 --> 00:14:53,435
ELI'S THE BEST WRITER
IN THE CLASS.

399
00:14:53,519 --> 00:14:55,562
IMOGEN:
OBVIOUSLY!

400
00:14:55,646 --> 00:14:57,147
FIONA:
AND I THINK WE SHOULD
GIVE HIM A CHANCE

401
00:14:57,231 --> 00:14:59,483
TO COME UP WITH SOME IDEAS.

402
00:15:00,484 --> 00:15:01,735
I'M IN.

403
00:15:01,818 --> 00:15:03,904
MS. DAWES:
I THINK WE'VE FOUND
OUR DIRECTOR.

404
00:15:03,987 --> 00:15:05,364
FIONA:
ME?

405
00:15:05,447 --> 00:15:08,158
OH, I'M NOT SURE...
I'M NOT MY BROTHER.

406
00:15:08,242 --> 00:15:09,701
MS. DAWES:
THEN THIS IS THE PERFECT
OPPORTUNITY TO SHOW US

407
00:15:09,785 --> 00:15:11,328
WHO YOU ARE.

408
00:15:11,411 --> 00:15:14,081
CLASS, ALL IN FAVOUR
OF ELI, THE WRITER,

409
00:15:14,164 --> 00:15:16,458
FIONA, THE DIRECTOR?

410
00:15:16,542 --> 00:15:18,544
STUDENTS:
YEAH. FOR SURE! FINE.

411
00:15:18,627 --> 00:15:19,878
GUY:
YEP.

412
00:15:19,962 --> 00:15:23,090
OKAY, WE'VE GOT A LOT OF WORK
AHEAD OF US!

413
00:15:23,173 --> 00:15:26,009
♪♪♪

414
00:15:26,093 --> 00:15:27,886
♪ Window in ♪

415
00:15:27,970 --> 00:15:29,972
♪ Window out ♪

416
00:15:34,268 --> 00:15:35,644
♪ These are the wars
we are in doubt ♪

417
00:15:35,727 --> 00:15:37,521
THINK YOU COULD HURRY UP
IN THERE?

418
00:15:40,607 --> 00:15:42,776
WHAT'RE YOU STARING AT?

419
00:15:44,111 --> 00:15:45,112
(SIGHS)

420
00:15:50,742 --> 00:15:52,411
♪ Burning with truth ♪

421
00:15:52,494 --> 00:15:54,329
♪ You're waking up under ♪

422
00:15:57,124 --> 00:15:59,918
♪ As a fallen tree ♪

423
00:16:01,170 --> 00:16:03,755
YOU'VE GOT FRIENDS
IN HIGH PLACES.

424
00:16:03,839 --> 00:16:04,798
I'M SORRY?

425
00:16:04,882 --> 00:16:06,717
I GOT REAMED OUT BY
THE STUDENT COUNCIL PRESIDENT

426
00:16:06,800 --> 00:16:09,052
FOR HAVING NO GRADE TENS
ON MY NEWSPAPER STAFF.

427
00:16:09,136 --> 00:16:10,679
I DIDN'T ASK SAV
TO DO ANYTHING.

428
00:16:10,762 --> 00:16:12,931
YOU DIDN'T ASK SAV
FOR A FAVOUR?

429
00:16:13,015 --> 00:16:15,851
THE OLDER BROTHER
OF YOUR BFF?

430
00:16:15,934 --> 00:16:17,436
WHAT DO YOU WANT, KATIE?

431
00:16:17,519 --> 00:16:18,812
I WANT...

432
00:16:19,813 --> 00:16:20,731
TO WELCOME YOU
TO THE STAFF

433
00:16:20,814 --> 00:16:22,941
OF THE DEGRASSI NEWSPAPER.

434
00:16:23,025 --> 00:16:24,818
NEXT MEETING'S TOMORROW
AT LUNCH.

435
00:16:24,902 --> 00:16:25,861
(GASPS)

436
00:16:25,944 --> 00:16:28,614
LOOK, I'M NOT ONE
TO HOLD GRUDGES.

437
00:16:28,697 --> 00:16:30,449
TOMORROW'S A NEW DAY
FOR US, OKAY?

438
00:16:30,532 --> 00:16:31,742
OKAY, AGREED.

439
00:16:31,825 --> 00:16:32,993
GREAT!

440
00:16:33,076 --> 00:16:36,121
AND HEY, I'VE GOT THE PERFECT
FIRST ASSIGNMENT FOR YOU.

441
00:16:36,205 --> 00:16:37,581
LAY IT ON ME.

442
00:16:37,664 --> 00:16:39,333
I JUST GOT A TEXT THAT
THE GRADE 11 DRAMA CLASS

443
00:16:39,416 --> 00:16:41,752
HAS CHOSEN THE WRITER
FOR THE SCHOOL PLAY.

444
00:16:41,835 --> 00:16:43,629
ELI SOMETHING OR OTHER?

445
00:16:43,712 --> 00:16:45,088
YOU KNOW HIM,
RIGHT?

446
00:16:45,172 --> 00:16:47,508
EX-BOYFRIEND, PERHAPS?

447
00:16:48,509 --> 00:16:49,593
YEAH.

448
00:16:49,676 --> 00:16:51,386
GOOD, BECAUSE YOU'RE GONNA
BE COVERING THE PLAY

449
00:16:51,470 --> 00:16:53,222
FROM NOW UNTIL
CLOSING NIGHT.

450
00:16:53,305 --> 00:16:54,223
BUT MAYBE-

451
00:16:54,306 --> 00:16:56,892
WHAT?
IS THERE A PROBLEM?

452
00:16:59,895 --> 00:17:01,688
NO.

453
00:17:01,772 --> 00:17:02,814
THERE'S NO PROBLEM.

454
00:17:02,898 --> 00:17:03,941
GOOD.

455
00:17:04,024 --> 00:17:05,275
KEEP YOUR SCHEDULE OPEN.

456
00:17:05,359 --> 00:17:09,196
YOU'RE GONNA BE SPENDING
LOTS OF TIME WITH ELI.

457
00:17:09,279 --> 00:17:10,280
(SIGHS)

458
00:17:15,619 --> 00:17:18,455
FIONA:
SO WICKED'S A FANTASY,
BUT STILL SO RELATABLE.

459
00:17:18,539 --> 00:17:19,665
AND ELPHABA MAY BE A WITCH,

460
00:17:19,748 --> 00:17:20,666
BUT SHE STILL HAD
THE SAME PROBLEMS

461
00:17:20,749 --> 00:17:22,543
FITTING IN AT SCHOOL
AS WE DO.

462
00:17:22,626 --> 00:17:23,585
ELI:
MAYBE THAT COULD BE OUR THEME.

463
00:17:23,669 --> 00:17:24,962
(SCOOTER RUMBLES)

464
00:17:25,963 --> 00:17:27,631
I...GOTTA GO.

465
00:17:27,714 --> 00:17:29,049
WE'LL TALK MORE ABOUT THIS
TOMORROW, OKAY?

466
00:17:29,132 --> 00:17:30,634
ELI:
GOT IT.

467
00:17:34,429 --> 00:17:36,181
HEY.
HI.

468
00:17:37,182 --> 00:17:38,392
I'M SORRY FOR SNAPPING
AT YOU,

469
00:17:38,475 --> 00:17:42,813
I WAS HAVING...
A REALLY ROUGH DAY.

470
00:17:42,896 --> 00:17:44,481
IT HAPPENS.

471
00:17:44,565 --> 00:17:46,400
APOLOGY ACCEPTED?

472
00:17:46,483 --> 00:17:47,776
YOU'RE LUCKY YOU'RE CUTE!

473
00:17:47,860 --> 00:17:49,403
(LAUGHS)

474
00:17:49,486 --> 00:17:51,321
SO, DID YOU...

475
00:17:51,405 --> 00:17:53,532
MAKE UP WITH
YOUR GIRLFRIEND?

476
00:17:53,615 --> 00:17:55,826
OH, ELISE ISN'T MY GIRLFRIEND.

477
00:17:56,827 --> 00:17:59,204
SHE, UH,
SHE WAS MY ROOMMATE.

478
00:18:00,205 --> 00:18:01,373
(SIGHS)

479
00:18:01,456 --> 00:18:04,168
I HAVE ALL THIS SCHOOL DEBT,

480
00:18:04,251 --> 00:18:08,755
AND I HAVEN'T BEEN ABLE
TO MAKE RENT IN A FEW MONTHS.

481
00:18:09,756 --> 00:18:11,175
AND SHE KICKED ME OUT,

482
00:18:11,258 --> 00:18:12,885
SO I HAVE NOWHERE TO GO.

483
00:18:12,968 --> 00:18:13,927
YOU'RE HOMELESS?

484
00:18:14,011 --> 00:18:14,928
THIS ISN'T YOUR PROBLEM,

485
00:18:15,012 --> 00:18:17,055
AND I DIDN'T COME HERE
TO LAY MY CRAP ON YOU.

486
00:18:17,139 --> 00:18:19,224
HEY, THAT'S WHAT FRIENDS
ARE FOR, RIGHT?

487
00:18:19,308 --> 00:18:21,018
DO YOU WANNA GRAB A CUP
OF COFFEE AFTER SCHOOL,

488
00:18:21,101 --> 00:18:22,102
AND TALK ABOUT IT?

489
00:18:22,186 --> 00:18:24,521
I'D LOVE A COFFEE,

490
00:18:24,605 --> 00:18:26,690
BUT I DON'T WANNA TALK
ABOUT IT.

491
00:18:26,773 --> 00:18:28,483
FINE, WE CAN TALK ABOUT
SOMETHING ELSE.

492
00:18:28,567 --> 00:18:30,527
I ACTUALLY HAD
AN AMAZING MORNING.

493
00:18:30,611 --> 00:18:32,613
REALLY?
WHAT AMAZINGNESS HAPPENED?

494
00:18:32,696 --> 00:18:35,282
WELL, UH, MY DRAMA CLASS
IS PUTTING ON THE SCHOOL PLAY,

495
00:18:35,365 --> 00:18:37,534
AND GUESS WHO'S DIRECTING IT?

496
00:18:37,618 --> 00:18:39,369
OKAY, DON'T BOTHER GUESSING!
IT'S ME!

497
00:18:39,453 --> 00:18:40,621
(LAUGHS)

498
00:18:41,788 --> 00:18:43,373
(MUSIC PLAYS)

499
00:18:49,296 --> 00:18:50,297
(DOOR CLICKS SHUT)

500
00:18:50,380 --> 00:18:51,298
(LOCK CLICKS)

501
00:18:55,552 --> 00:18:58,347
SAV: (FROM CONTROL BOOTH)
DAVE! YOU CAN'T BE IN THERE!

502
00:18:58,430 --> 00:19:00,265
I'VE GOT A SHOW TO DO.

503
00:19:01,642 --> 00:19:02,643
(SIGHS DEEPLY)

504
00:19:04,561 --> 00:19:06,063
(KEYS CLICK)

505
00:19:06,146 --> 00:19:08,148
HEY, DEGRASSI, HOW ARE YOU?
IT'S DAVE TURNER.

506
00:19:08,232 --> 00:19:09,233
I HAVE...

507
00:19:10,692 --> 00:19:13,320
MR. SIMPSON:
DAVE? DAVE! OPEN THE DOOR!

508
00:19:13,403 --> 00:19:15,489
LOOK, I HAVE SOMETHING
YOU'RE GONNA WANNA HEAR.

509
00:19:21,620 --> 00:19:23,413
FIONA:
WE STILL ON FOR COFFEE
BEFORE MY CLASS?

510
00:19:23,497 --> 00:19:25,082
MAYBE A SCOOTER RIDE BEFORE?

511
00:19:25,165 --> 00:19:26,500
CHARLIE:
SURE, I'LL PICK YOU UP.

512
00:19:26,583 --> 00:19:27,835
FIONA:
BYE, CHARLIE.

513
00:19:27,918 --> 00:19:29,294
CHARLIE:
BYE, FI.

514
00:19:31,129 --> 00:19:33,340
THAT'S A PRETTY CRAZY DANCE
THERE, CRAZY LEGS!

515
00:19:33,423 --> 00:19:35,175
WELL,
IT WAS A CRAZY MORNING!

516
00:19:35,259 --> 00:19:36,510
UH...

517
00:19:36,593 --> 00:19:38,512
I HEARD YOU'RE DIRECTING
THE PLAY!

518
00:19:38,595 --> 00:19:39,513
FIONA:
OH YEAH, THAT TOO!

519
00:19:39,596 --> 00:19:40,556
THAT TOO?

520
00:19:40,639 --> 00:19:41,557
YOU WERE RIGHT,
HOLLY J,

521
00:19:41,640 --> 00:19:42,808
I JUST NEEDED
TO PUT MYSELF OUT THERE,

522
00:19:42,891 --> 00:19:44,226
AND PEOPLE CAME TO ME.

523
00:19:44,309 --> 00:19:46,061
I'M SO GLAD YOU HAVE
SOMETHING KEEPING YOU BUSY.

524
00:19:46,144 --> 00:19:47,187
THIS WAY YOU WON'T SPEND
TOO MUCH TIME

525
00:19:47,271 --> 00:19:49,439
PINING AFTER CHARLIE
FROM AFAR.

526
00:19:49,523 --> 00:19:51,191
YEAH, WELL,
THERE'S NO NEED FOR PINING.

527
00:19:51,275 --> 00:19:54,069
AND IT WON'T EXACTLY BE
FROM AFAR.

528
00:19:54,152 --> 00:19:55,654
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

529
00:19:55,737 --> 00:19:57,030
CHARLIE'S LOSING
HER APARTMENT,

530
00:19:57,114 --> 00:20:00,742
SO I SAID SHE COULD
MOVE IN WITH ME.

531
00:20:00,826 --> 00:20:03,245
FRIENDS DON'T LET FRIENDS
BE HOMELESS, HOLLY J!

532
00:20:03,328 --> 00:20:05,706
YOU HAVE A HUGE CRUSH
ON HER, FIONA!

533
00:20:05,789 --> 00:20:08,041
HOW CAN YOU POSSIBLY LIVE
TOGETHER PLATONICALLY?

534
00:20:08,125 --> 00:20:10,961
AND WHAT WILL
MAMA COYNE THINK?

535
00:20:11,044 --> 00:20:13,589
SHE ALWAYS TAUGHT ME
TO BE CHARITABLE.

536
00:20:13,672 --> 00:20:14,673
(LAUGHS)

537
00:20:16,383 --> 00:20:17,301
FOR THOSE OF YOU
WHO DON'T KNOW,

538
00:20:17,384 --> 00:20:18,719
THE OTHER DAY I TALKED ABOUT
HOW I WAS SURPRISED

539
00:20:18,802 --> 00:20:22,347
THAT TRANSGENDERED KIDS GOT
TO USE THE REGULAR BATHROOM.

540
00:20:22,431 --> 00:20:25,350
I RAN INTO THAT SITUATION,
AND I WAS FREAKED, OKAY?

541
00:20:25,434 --> 00:20:27,227
I CAN ADMIT THAT.

542
00:20:27,311 --> 00:20:28,937
I-I USED STUPID,
HATEFUL LANGUAGE,

543
00:20:29,021 --> 00:20:31,607
AND I OFFENDED
A LOT OF PEOPLE -

544
00:20:31,690 --> 00:20:33,942
MY CO-HOST,
IN PARTICULAR -

545
00:20:34,026 --> 00:20:35,986
AND I'M REALLY SORRY.

546
00:20:36,069 --> 00:20:37,070
I SHOULD'VE TOLD HIM
HOW I FELT,

547
00:20:37,154 --> 00:20:38,572
AND, YOU KNOW,

548
00:20:38,655 --> 00:20:40,282
STARTED A DIALOGUE.

549
00:20:41,325 --> 00:20:43,202
ADAM:
SIR? JUST LET HIM FINISH.

550
00:20:43,285 --> 00:20:45,621
DAVE:
AND IF YOU GUYS LET ME
KEEP DOING THE SHOW,

551
00:20:45,704 --> 00:20:47,331
THAT'S WHAT I'LL DO.

552
00:20:47,414 --> 00:20:49,249
TALK ABOUT THE TOUGH STUFF.

553
00:20:49,333 --> 00:20:50,501
ASK QUESTIONS,

554
00:20:50,584 --> 00:20:54,004
TRY AND UNDERSTAND,
INSTEAD OF JUDGE.

555
00:20:54,087 --> 00:20:56,507
SO, ADAM TORRES,
YOU'RE DOWN FOR THIS?

556
00:20:58,008 --> 00:20:59,843
UH... DEPENDS.

557
00:21:01,762 --> 00:21:03,680
ARE YOU GONNA BE PULLING
ANY OTHER SKELETONS

558
00:21:03,764 --> 00:21:04,973
OUT OF MY CLOSET?

559
00:21:05,057 --> 00:21:07,935
DAVE:
NOPE, JUST WANT HONEST TALK.

560
00:21:08,018 --> 00:21:10,521
SO THE QUESTION HERE IS...

561
00:21:10,604 --> 00:21:12,564
WHAT MAKES YOU A GUY, EXACTLY?

562
00:21:12,648 --> 00:21:14,274
TELL US.

563
00:21:14,358 --> 00:21:16,193
NO, THE QUESTION IS...

564
00:21:17,402 --> 00:21:18,946
WHAT MAKES YOU A GUY?

565
00:21:19,029 --> 00:21:20,197
(LAUGHS)

566
00:21:20,280 --> 00:21:22,282
OKAY, I DESERVED THAT.

567
00:21:22,366 --> 00:21:24,743
LOOK, YOU KNOW
YOU'RE A GUY,

568
00:21:24,826 --> 00:21:26,453
SO DO I.

569
00:21:26,537 --> 00:21:28,580
BUT I GOT WRONG EQUIPMENT.

570
00:21:28,664 --> 00:21:29,873
DAVE:
WHAT, YOU CAN'T EXCHANGE?

571
00:21:29,957 --> 00:21:31,375
(LAUGHS)

572
00:21:31,458 --> 00:21:33,252
MAYBE SOME DAY.

573
00:21:33,335 --> 00:21:36,463
ENOUGH TALK,
THE PEOPLE WANT TUNES!

574
00:21:36,547 --> 00:21:38,298
DAVE:
ALL RIGHT.

575
00:21:38,382 --> 00:21:39,550
WE'LL BE BACK.

576
00:21:39,633 --> 00:21:40,801
♪ I'll take you away ♪

577
00:21:40,884 --> 00:21:42,469
♪ I can take you away ♪

578
00:21:42,553 --> 00:21:44,179
♪ Take my hand don't be shy ♪

579
00:21:44,263 --> 00:21:46,306
♪ Please don't beg,
please don't cry ♪

580
00:21:46,390 --> 00:21:48,392
♪ I'll take you away,
I can take you away... ♪

